{
  "texts": [
    "Two often disregarded aspects of this text data are: (i) the demographics and intentions of its creators, and (ii) the intended audience for whom it was written.",
    "Both factors can significantly influence the composition and distribution of the data, and consequently, the resulting behavior of a user-centric language model (e.g., children).",
    "With the aforementioned requirements for language models tailored for children, we curated high-quality, kid-appropriate content specifically written for children and occasionally by them.",
    "This content was meticulously reviewed and validated 2 Information about annotators can be found as an answer of the question \"Who completes the tasks on Amazon Mechanical Turk and how do they complete them?\" in this link.",
    "3 We use the terms \"kids\" and \"children\" interchangeably."
  ]
}